734
1:2:16,722 --> 1:2:20,402
You said,
"Can't rain all the time."


735
1:2:20,402 --> 1:2:33,4
That is from your song, right?


736
1:2:33,4 --> 1:2:38,319
- ( Cawing )
- Come on, Eric. I know you're here.


737
1:2:38,319 --> 1:2:45,198
I miss you...
and Shelly.


738
1:2:45,198 --> 1:2:50,278
Get so lonely
all by myself.


739
1:2:50,278 --> 1:2:54,797
The hell with you.
I thought you cared.


740
1:2:54,797 --> 1:3:8,555
Sarah, I do care.


741
1:3:8,555 --> 1:3:10,675
That's him.
That's him!


742
1:3:10,675 --> 1:3:13,955
But he looked different. He was painted
up white like some kind of dead whore.


743
1:3:13,955 --> 1:3:17,154
I seen him. T-bird sent me in
for some road beers, right?


744
1:3:17,154 --> 1:3:19,674
Then he took him away.
But I chased him down.


745
1:3:19,674 --> 1:3:22,433
And he flash fried T-bird
to his fucking car!


746
1:3:22,433 --> 1:3:25,873
Aw, T-bird!
Here's to you, buddy.


747
1:3:25,873 --> 1:3:30,912
Maybe we oughta just videotape this.
Play it back in slow motion.


748
1:3:30,912 --> 1:3:35,392
- Fire it up! Fire it up!
- You see the grave?


749
1:3:35,392 --> 1:3:37,951
- Empty.
- Fire it--


750
1:3:37,951 --> 1:3:39,871
Grave?
What grave?


751
1:3:39,871 --> 1:3:42,71
What about
my fucking grave?


752
1:3:42,71 --> 1:3:43,431
- ( Screams )
- Three out of four.


753
1:3:43,431 --> 1:3:46,63
He's working his way back
to this speed freak right here.


754
1:3:46,63 --> 1:3:49,23
It's not fair.
It's Funboy's fault.


755
1:3:49,23 --> 1:3:52,349
That boy was out of control.
T-bird, he came in, he says...
( Whistles )


756
1:3:52,349 --> 1:3:55,589
..."Waste them both." And now
this ghost gonna kill my ass next!


757
1:3:55,589 --> 1:3:59,388
( Groaning )


758
1:3:59,388 --> 1:4:2,428
This ghost gonna
kill my ass next.


759
1:4:2,428 --> 1:4:6,108
- This ghost gonna kill--
- Hey.


760
1:4:6,108 --> 1:4:9,827
That ain't no ghost.


761
1:4:9,827 --> 1:4:12,907
- They have all arrived.
- Watch him.


762
1:4:12,907 --> 1:4:16,266
We might need him.


763
1:4:16,266 --> 1:4:30,824
Ghost gonna kill my--


764
1:4:30,824 --> 1:4:34,664
He like his plain
or with onions?


765
1:4:34,664 --> 1:4:38,23
Fine.
Don't talk to me.


766
1:4:38,23 --> 1:4:42,23
When someone's dead,
they can't come back, can they?


767
1:4:42,23 --> 1:4:44,582
That's what I thought.


768
1:4:44,582 --> 1:4:47,302
Are you referring
to anyone in particular?


769
1:4:47,302 --> 1:4:49,542
You'll just think
I'm nuts.


770
1:4:49,542 --> 1:4:53,101
Yeah, well, then maybe
they'll have to lock us both up.


771
1:4:53,101 --> 1:4:58,301
- You see him too?
- I saw somebody.


772
1:4:58,301 --> 1:5:1,74
Maybe it was
your fairy godfather.


773
1:5:1,74 --> 1:5:4,62
Eric didn't come back for me.


774
1:5:4,62 --> 1:5:9,259
He can't be my friend anymore
because I'm alive.


775
1:5:9,259 --> 1:5:12,379
You want a friend
to walk you home?


776
1:5:12,379 --> 1:5:41,575
** ( Electric Guitar )


777
1:5:41,575 --> 1:5:56,973
- ( Screaming )
- * I am the wicked
I am the wave of the future *


778
1:5:56,973 --> 1:5:58,892
( Woman ) * Being crucified *


779
1:5:58,892 --> 1:6:3,92
* You things, things
things of the flesh *


780
1:6:3,92 --> 1:6:5,772
* Do it slow *


781
1:6:5,772 --> 1:6:9,971
* Down avenues "cut me" *


782
1:6:9,971 --> 1:6:13,571
* Lust my eyes *


783
1:6:13,571 --> 1:6:19,65
* Licking lips encouraging
Mr. Careworn *


784
1:6:19,65 --> 1:6:25,609
* To gaze upon the screen bask on *


785
1:6:25,609 --> 1:6:39,47
* After the flesh **


786
1:6:39,47 --> 1:6:42,567
( Whimpering )


787
1:6:42,567 --> 1:6:45,446
Boys.


788
1:6:45,446 --> 1:6:48,806
It seems our friend T-bird won't be
joining us this evening...


789
1:6:48,806 --> 1:6:50,886
on account of
a slight case of death.


790
1:6:50,886 --> 1:6:52,845
- ( Men Chuckling )
- You wanna sit down?


791
1:6:52,845 --> 1:6:58,45
- ( Groaning )
- Well, well, well.


792
1:6:58,45 --> 1:7:1,44
Devil's Night is
upon us again.


793
1:7:1,44 --> 1:7:2,964
I thought we'd throw
a little party...


794
1:7:2,964 --> 1:7:6,163
start a bunch of fires,
make a little profit.


795
1:7:6,163 --> 1:7:8,403
I like the pretty lights.


796
1:7:8,403 --> 1:7:11,203
( Laughing )


797
1:7:11,203 --> 1:7:15,2
Problem is, it's all been done before.
You see what I'm saying?


798
1:7:15,2 --> 1:7:20,82
- That's no reason to quit.
- Wrong. Best reason to quit.


799
1:7:20,82 --> 1:7:22,441
Only reason to quit.


800
1:7:22,441 --> 1:7:27,801
A man has an idea.


801
1:7:27,801 --> 1:7:30,4
The idea attracts others...


802
1:7:30,4 --> 1:7:32,12
like-minded.


803
1:7:32,12 --> 1:7:34,2
The idea expands.


804
1:7:34,2 --> 1:7:37,759
The idea becomes
an institution.


805
1:7:37,759 --> 1:7:40,399
What was the idea?


806
1:7:40,399 --> 1:7:44,78
See, that's what's
been bothering me, boys.


807
1:7:44,78 --> 1:7:46,838
But I'll tell ya, when I used
to think about the idea itself...


808
1:7:46,838 --> 1:7:49,878
it'd put a big old smile on my face.


809
1:7:49,878 --> 1:7:52,37
You see, gentlemen...


810
1:7:52,37 --> 1:7:56,917
greed is for amateurs.


811
1:7:56,917 --> 1:8:1,956
Disorder, chaos, anarchy...


812
1:8:1,956 --> 1:8:4,516
now that's fun!


813
1:8:4,516 --> 1:8:6,795
- What about Devil's Night?
- What about it?


814
1:8:6,795 --> 1:8:10,115
I started the first fires
in this goddamn city.


815
1:8:10,115 --> 1:8:13,154
Before I knew it, every charlatan
and shitheel was imitating me.


816
1:8:13,154 --> 1:8:16,514
Do you know
what they got now?


817
1:8:16,514 --> 1:8:20,673
Devil's Night greeting cards.


818
1:8:20,673 --> 1:8:23,553
Isn't that precious?


819
1:8:23,553 --> 1:8:25,633
Yeah.


820
1:8:25,633 --> 1:8:30,272
The idea has become
the institution, boys.


821
1:8:30,272 --> 1:8:32,312
Time to move along.


822
1:8:32,312 --> 1:8:34,712
You don't want us to do
"Light My Fire" time for the whole city?


823
1:8:34,712 --> 1:8:37,151
No.


824
1:8:37,151 --> 1:8:39,711
No, I want you to set
a fire so goddamn big...


825
1:8:39,711 --> 1:8:42,751
the gods will notice us again.
That's what I'm saying.


826
1:8:42,751 --> 1:8:45,31
I want all of you boys to be able
to look me straight in the eye...


827
1:8:45,31 --> 1:8:49,63
one more time and say,
"Are we having fun or what?"


828
1:8:49,63 --> 1:8:51,709
- Hey, you! What's your name?
- Huh?


829
1:8:51,709 --> 1:8:53,629
Skank!
You don't feel that?


830
1:8:53,629 --> 1:8:56,869
- I feel like a little worm
on a big fucking hook.
- ( All Laughing )


831
1:8:56,869 --> 1:8:59,268
"I feel like a little worm
on a big fucking hook."


832
1:8:59,268 --> 1:9:3,548
Well, boy, your mama
must be damn proud of you!


833
1:9:3,548 --> 1:9:5,827
- ( Crow Caws )
- ( Gasps )


834
1:9:5,827 --> 1:9:9,707
How the hell did
that thing get in here?


835
1:9:9,707 --> 1:9:12,187
- Gentlemen.
- ( Skank Screams )


836
1:9:12,187 --> 1:9:20,985
( Skank Whimpering ) Let me go!
Let me go! I gotta go!


837
1:9:20,985 --> 1:9:24,665
You're him, huh?
The avenger.


838
1:9:24,665 --> 1:9:27,145
The killer of killers.


839
1:9:27,145 --> 1:9:29,944
- Nice outfit.
- ( Whimpering )


840
1:9:29,944 --> 1:9:31,984
I'm not sure
about the face though.


841
1:9:31,984 --> 1:9:34,24
I just want him.


842
1:9:34,24 --> 1:9:37,383
- ( Whimpering )
- Well, you can't have him.


843
1:9:37,383 --> 1:9:41,943
Well...


844
1:9:41,943 --> 1:9:45,822
I see you have
made your decision.


845
1:9:45,822 --> 1:9:47,782
Now let's see you enforce it.


846
1:9:47,782 --> 1:9:56,941
Aw, this is already boring the shit
out of me. Kill him!


847
1:9:56,941 --> 1:10:0,78
Ooh, that had to hurt.


848
1:10:0,78 --> 1:10:3,54
- ( All Laughing )
- Well, that's that.


849
1:10:3,54 --> 1:10:8,819
- ( Laughing Continues )
- That guy was crazy.


850
1:10:8,819 --> 1:10:12,938
( Caws )


851
1:10:12,938 --> 1:10:14,738
He's gone.
( Screams )


852
1:10:14,738 --> 1:10:22,377
( Screaming, Gunfire )


853
1:10:22,377 --> 1:10:29,256
Get him!


854
1:10:29,256 --> 1:10:40,575
- ( Whimpering )
- ( Gunfire )


855
1:10:40,575 --> 1:10:47,134
Right here! Here, help me!
He's gonna kill me!


856
1:10:47,134 --> 1:11:4,812
Jesus Christ!


857
1:11:4,812 --> 1:11:37,887
Hey!


858
1:11:37,887 --> 1:11:51,45
You're all going to die.


859
1:11:51,45 --> 1:11:54,525
( Screaming )


860
1:11:54,525 --> 1:12:9,3
( Man ) Get the fuck outta here!


861
1:12:9,3 --> 1:12:11,563
( Crowd Screaming )


862
1:12:11,563 --> 1:12:21,241
( Whimpering, Gasping )


863
1:12:21,241 --> 1:12:26,81
( Whimpering )


864
1:12:26,81 --> 1:12:31,56
( Screams )


865
1:12:31,56 --> 1:12:34,44
Guess it's not a good day
to be a bad guy, huh, Skank?


866
1:12:34,44 --> 1:12:37,599
I'm not Skank.
There's Skank right there.


867
1:12:37,599 --> 1:12:41,399
- Skank's dead.
- That's right.


868
1:12:41,399 --> 1:12:43,198
( Screaming ) No!


869
1:12:43,198 --> 1:12:47,558
( Whimpering )


870
1:12:47,558 --> 1:12:52,357
- ( Body Crashing )
- What in the crap--


871
1:12:52,357 --> 1:12:54,957
- Don't move!
- Hold it!


872
1:12:54,957 --> 1:13:4,835
That's all she wrote!
Move and we shoot!


873
1:13:4,835 --> 1:13:6,955
( Siren Blaring )


874
1:13:6,955 --> 1:13:9,795
You are surrounded by police units.
Do not attempt to escape.


875
1:13:9,795 --> 1:13:13,34
( Gunfire Continues )


876
1:13:13,34 --> 1:13:16,594
- Stop running immediately.
- Holy shit!


877
1:13:16,594 --> 1:13:23,953
...arms and legs--


878
1:13:23,953 --> 1:14:7,507
Stop immediately.
Lie down, spread your arms and legs--


879
1:14:7,507 --> 1:14:16,186
- ( Tires Screeching )
- Come on! Move it!


880
1:14:16,186 --> 1:14:21,145
My advice:
Next time duck.


881
1:14:21,145 --> 1:14:23,505
So many cops, you'd think
they were giving away donuts.


882
1:14:23,505 --> 1:14:26,744
- ( Sirens Wailing )
- ( Brakes Screeching )


883
1:14:26,744 --> 1:14:32,504
- Shit!
- ( Door Opening )


884
1:14:32,504 --> 1:14:35,383
Oh. I knew you
were gonna do that.


885
1:14:35,383 --> 1:14:37,783
Look at that out there.


886
1:14:37,783 --> 1:14:40,663
The whole city oughta be
in flames by now.


887
1:14:40,663 --> 1:14:43,822
Sky oughta be red.


888
1:14:43,822 --> 1:14:48,22
So that, I take it,
is the late, great Eric Draven.


889
1:14:48,22 --> 1:14:53,581
He has power, but it is power
you can take from him.


890
1:14:53,581 --> 1:14:56,5
- I like him already.
- The crow...


891
1:14:56,5 --> 1:15:0,86
is his link between
the land of the living...


892
1:15:0,86 --> 1:15:3,18
and the realm of the dead.


893
1:15:3,18 --> 1:15:7,579
So, kill the crow
and destroy the man.


894
1:15:7,579 --> 1:15:31,656
Hmm.


895
1:15:31,656 --> 1:15:33,656
I'm coming home, Shelly.


896
1:15:33,656 --> 1:15:35,815
( Laughing )


897
1:15:35,815 --> 1:15:41,374
( Laughing Continues )


898
1:15:41,374 --> 1:15:47,334
( Chuckles )


899
1:15:47,334 --> 1:15:51,453
( Children Laughing, Hooting )


900
1:15:51,453 --> 1:16:20,649
( Laughing )


901
1:16:20,649 --> 1:16:23,49
You're gonna say
I shouldn't be in the cemetery...


902
1:16:23,49 --> 1:16:25,89
in the middle
of the night, right?


903
1:16:25,89 --> 1:16:26,848
Safest place in the world to be.


904
1:16:26,848 --> 1:16:31,488
It's 'cause everybody's dead.
I knew you'd come here.


905
1:16:31,488 --> 1:16:35,567
It's really late, Sarah.


906
1:16:35,567 --> 1:16:38,327
You didn't say good-bye.


907
1:16:38,327 --> 1:16:42,206
You're just gonna have
to forgive me for that.


908
1:16:42,206 --> 1:16:52,325
And you're never coming back.


909
1:16:52,325 --> 1:16:59,4
I gave this to Shelly once.


910
1:16:59,4 --> 1:17:5,723
I think she'd like you
to have it.


911
1:17:5,723 --> 1:17:7,963
This way you'll
always remember her.


912
1:17:7,963 --> 1:17:27,84
I'll never take it off.


913
1:17:27,84 --> 1:17:37,399
I better go sneak
back in the house.


914
1:17:37,399 --> 1:17:58,436
Bye.


915
1:17:58,436 --> 1:18:2,996
- ( Muffled Screaming )
- Shh! Shh!


916
1:18:2,996 --> 1:18:5,355
Shh. Take it easy, sweetheart.


917
1:18:5,355 --> 1:18:11,954
( Muffled Screaming Continues )


918
1:18:11,954 --> 1:18:27,72
Come on.
Come on.


919
1:18:27,72 --> 1:18:32,552
What is that? Some sort of souvenir
there from your pal?


920
1:18:32,552 --> 1:18:41,71
I'll just keep it for good luck.
What do you say, hmm?


921
1:18:41,71 --> 1:18:55,748
Her eyes are so innocent.


922
1:18:55,748 --> 1:18:57,668
- ( Sarah ) Eric!
- ( Caws )


923
1:18:57,668 --> 1:19:4,907
Eric, help! Eric!


924
1:19:4,907 --> 1:19:9,867
( Thunderclap )


925
1:19:9,867 --> 1:19:25,65
( Crow Caws )


926
1:19:25,65 --> 1:19:39,303
( Crow Flapping, Caws )


927
1:19:39,303 --> 1:19:42,462
Quick impression for ya.


928
1:19:42,462 --> 1:19:46,102
Caw! Caw! Bang!
Fuck, I'm dead!


929
1:19:46,102 --> 1:19:49,381
Give me the girl
and I'll let you walk out of here.


930
1:19:49,381 --> 1:19:52,381
( Inhales )
Well, well.


931
1:19:52,381 --> 1:20:0,26
Why don't you just give me a minute
to think about that, huh?


932
1:20:0,26 --> 1:20:3,619
( Cawing )


933
1:20:3,619 --> 1:20:11,578
Nah. Fuck it.


934
1:20:11,578 --> 1:20:13,938
( Chuckles )


935
1:20:13,938 --> 1:20:19,57
Aw, fuck.


936
1:20:19,57 --> 1:20:22,937
( Muffled Screaming )


937
1:20:22,937 --> 1:20:27,376
Well, well, well. It does seem to me
that our little life has undergone...


938
1:20:27,376 --> 1:20:31,136
a rather significant change in the past
few minutes now. Wouldn't you agree?


939
1:20:31,136 --> 1:20:35,215
( Groaning )


940
1:20:35,215 --> 1:20:41,854
Well, for a ghost,
you bleed just fine.


941
1:20:41,854 --> 1:20:45,614
- It's still alive.
- Well, then kill it!


942
1:20:45,614 --> 1:21:30,968
Bye-bye, birdie.


943
1:21:30,968 --> 1:21:33,47
Ah, shit.


944
1:21:33,47 --> 1:21:35,127
Well, just came by
to pay my respects...


945
1:21:35,127 --> 1:21:37,167
and here you are
getting all shot up again.


946
1:21:37,167 --> 1:21:39,726
- They've taken Sarah.
- How many?


947
1:21:39,726 --> 1:21:41,686
Two more.
( Groans )


948
1:21:41,686 --> 1:21:43,686
I can handle it.
Don't worry.


949
1:21:43,686 --> 1:21:46,166
I'm not worried.
Look, here's the plan.


950
1:21:46,166 --> 1:21:48,885
You stay in front, and when they
run out of ammo, I'll arrest 'em.


951
1:21:48,885 --> 1:21:55,4
That sounds like a great plan.
There's just one problem.


952
1:21:55,4 --> 1:21:58,484
Oh, shit.
You're bleeding all over the place.


953
1:21:58,484 --> 1:22:0,524
I thought, you know,
you were invincible.


954
1:22:0,524 --> 1:22:3,923
I was.
I'm not anymore.


955
1:22:3,923 --> 1:22:8,43
( Sighs ) Well, I guess you really will
need my help, won't you?


956
1:22:8,43 --> 1:22:13,402
- Come on.
- ( Groaning )


957
1:22:13,402 --> 1:22:44,198
You take that.


958
1:22:44,198 --> 1:23:8,755
- You were supposed to stay behind me.
- I think I messed up.


959
1:23:8,755 --> 1:23:10,634
( Crow Caws )


960
1:23:10,634 --> 1:23:13,794
This is all the power
you ever had.


961
1:23:13,794 --> 1:23:15,874
Now it is mine.


962
1:23:15,874 --> 1:23:19,513
Pity there's not more time...


963
1:23:19,513 --> 1:23:23,393
- ( Gun Cocks )
- ...for us.


964
1:23:23,393 --> 1:23:30,512
( Woman Screaming )


965
1:23:30,512 --> 1:23:35,551
( Screaming )


966
1:23:35,551 --> 1:23:39,43
( Screaming Continues )


967
1:23:39,43 --> 1:23:44,19
( Sarah ) Help, Eric!
I'm scared!


968
1:23:44,19 --> 1:23:55,348
Let me go!


969
1:23:55,348 --> 1:23:58,788
Let her go!


970
1:23:58,788 --> 1:24:1,587
You can have me.
I won't fight you.


971
1:24:1,587 --> 1:24:3,267
You can have me.
I won't fight you.


972
1:24:3,267 --> 1:24:5,267
All right.


973
1:24:5,267 --> 1:24:10,866
- ( Sarah Screams )
- No!


974
1:24:10,866 --> 1:24:18,185
( Gasping, Groaning )


975
1:24:18,185 --> 1:24:20,225
( Crow Caws )


976
1:24:20,225 --> 1:24:22,545
( Thunderclap )


977
1:24:22,545 --> 1:24:24,864
( Gasping )


978
1:24:24,864 --> 1:24:45,742
- ( Thunderclap )
- ( Screams )


979
1:24:45,742 --> 1:24:48,581
( Swords Clanking )


980
